{"pageProps":{"data":{"news_id":"624","news_catgory":"1","hot_news":"0","news_push":"","news_on_top":"1","news_title":"研究：世界經濟為驅動氣候變遷關鍵因素","news_summary":"","image_path":"","news_des":null,"news_content":"<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>時間：<span lang='EN-US'>2020-01-23 08:57 &nbsp; </span>新聞引據、採訪：法新社&nbsp; 撰稿編輯：林柏宏</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span lang='EN-US' style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;&#10;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'><img alt='' src='/user_files/news_files/%E7%B6%93%E6%BF%9F%E8%88%87%E6%B0%A3%E5%80%99%E8%AE%8A%E9%81%B7.jpg' style='width: 800px; height: 600px;' /></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>太平洋島國吐瓦魯正面臨海平面上升的危機。<span lang='EN-US'>(pixabay</span>圖庫<span lang='EN-US'>)</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>環保聯盟今天<span lang='EN-US'>(23</span>日<span lang='EN-US'>)</span>表示，世界經濟是社會崩盤的直接原因，也是驅動氣候變遷的關鍵因素。這是相關單位首次對各國政府如何重現經濟的持續增長進行評估。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>「綠色經濟追蹤」<span lang='EN-US'>(The Green Economy Tracker</span>，暫譯<span lang='EN-US'>)</span>評估了各國在<span lang='EN-US'>5</span>個關鍵政策領域上的表現，包含如何解決不平等問題、以及在氣候暖化及海平面上升帶來的整體性風險之下，如何排定處理自然災害的優先順位。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>綠色經濟追蹤的格林菲爾德<span lang='EN-US'>(Oliver Greenfield)</span>在達弗斯<span lang='EN-US'>(Davos)</span>的峰會召開之際表示：「我們的全球經濟不適得其用。」</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>格林菲爾德表示：「不均等、貧窮、氣候變遷和生物多樣性的喪失不僅僅相互連結。它們是由同一原因引起的。」這即是看「經濟如何被組織、統領和管理」。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>全球的商界精英聚集在瑞士阿爾卑斯山度假勝地達弗斯，參加第<span lang='EN-US'>50</span>屆世界經濟論壇<span lang='EN-US'>(World Economic Forum)</span>，而目前的討論都聚焦在氣候議題上。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>在達弗斯的峰會前夕，世界經濟論壇發佈其年度的全球風險報告<span lang='EN-US'>(Global Risks Report)</span>，並調查了商界領袖主要擔憂的議題。報告指出，全球前五大經濟風險全與環境有關。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>慈善機構樂施會<span lang='EN-US'>(Oxfam)</span>於<span lang='EN-US'>20</span>日發佈報告、並聚焦在擴大的貧富差距。報告指出，全球億萬富翁的人數增加了一倍，這些有錢人的財富超越全球<span lang='EN-US'>60%</span>人口。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>綠色經濟追蹤表示，各國政府需要意識到，氣候和經濟有著錯綜複雜的連結。</span></p>\n\n<p><span lang='EN-US' style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='font-size:16px;'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;微軟正黑體&quot;,sans-serif'>資料來源：<span lang='EN-US'>https://www.rti.org.tw/news/view/id/2049122</span></span></span></p>\n","keyword":"","news_order_id":"0","create_date":"2020-01-30","clk_count":"30"}},"__N_SSG":true}